!! Example config (not bundled as shadow tiddlers)

The `example-config/` directory contains user-facing configuration examples. These are //not// shadow tiddlers ŌĆö users copy or adapt them into their wiki's `tiddlers/` directory.

|!File |!Role |
|`example-config/profiles.tid` |Example profile mapping (default ŌåÆ inbox template) |
|`example-config/rules.tid` |Example rule (stream-reply-default) |
|`example-config/tpl/inbox.tid` |Example template: inbox items with auto-title and tag |
|`example-config/tpl/stream-reply-default.tid` |Example template: stream reply with post-creation actions |
|`example-config/text-command/scan-filter.tid` |Example scan filter: `[tag[process]]` |
|`example-config/text-command/outbox-tag.tid` |Example outbox tag: `ext-outbox` |
|`example-config/text-command/targets.json` |Example registered targets: `["LLM", "Dodo"]` |
|`example-config/text-command/view-template.tid` |Example inline command display template |
|`example-config/text-command/delegate.tid` |Example cascade delegate for `--render` |
|`example-config/text-command/cascade/*.tid` |Example cascade selectors (LLM, Dodo, streams, default) |
|`example-config/text-command/ctx/*.tid` |Example context render templates (LLM, Dodo, streams, default) |

!! Restart rules

|!Change |!Restart needed? |
|`route.js` / `resolve.js` / `deserializer.js` |Yes ŌĆö JS modules loaded at boot |
|`profiles.tid` content |No ŌĆö re-read from wiki store per request |
|`rules.tid` content |No ŌĆö re-read from wiki store per request |
|Template tiddlers (`tpl-*.tid`) |No ŌĆö re-read from wiki store per request |
|Settings UI / doc tiddlers |No ŌĆö shadow tiddlers, but may need browser reload |
|`text-command.js` |Yes ŌĆö browser startup module loaded at boot |
|`filesystem-paths-setup.js` |Yes ŌĆö server startup module loaded at boot |
|Text-command config tiddlers |No ŌĆö re-read from wiki store per save |
|Context templates + cascade selectors |No ŌĆö wikitext shadow tiddlers, evaluated at render time |

!! External files

The `mywiki-cli` wrapper (sibling to `mywiki/`) is part of this plugin's workflow but lives outside the plugin directory:

|!File |!Role |
|`mywiki-cli/tiddlywiki.info` |CLI wrapper ŌĆö includes `mywiki` read-only via `includeWikis` |
|`mywiki-cli/tiddlers/$__config_Plugins_Disabled_$__plugins_rimir_filesystem-watcher.tid` |Disables filesystem-watcher so CLI process exits after import |

!! Debugging

!!! POST endpoint (fallback ŌĆö may be deprecated)

* Basic test: `curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/ext-connect/put-tiddler -H "Content-Type: application/json" -H "X-Requested-With: TiddlyWiki" -d '{"text": "test"}'`
* Check response: should return `{"status": "ok", "title": "Inbox/..."}`
* Verify on disk: look for new `.tid` files in `mywiki/tiddlers/`
* Check browser: tiddler appears after syncer poll (default 4s)
* Test actions: create a context tiddler with a `streams-default` field and `list` field, then send a request with `"context": ["ThatTiddler"]` ŌĆö verify the parent's `list` field is updated

!!! CLI import (deserializer)

* Basic test: `echo '{"text": "test"}' > /tmp/test.json && TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1 npx tiddlywiki mywiki --import /tmp/test.json application/x-rimir-ext-connect`
* Check console: should print `ext-connect: created "Inbox/..." ŌåÆ /path/to/file.tid`
* Verify file lands in `mywiki/tiddlers/`
* Process should exit cleanly (`TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1` prevents filesystem-watcher from hanging)
* With server running: verify filesystem-watcher picks up the file and it appears in browser

!! Key gotchas

* ''CSRF header required'': all requests need `X-Requested-With: TiddlyWiki` header
* ''`state.data` not `request.on("data")`'': TW's server framework pre-reads POST bodies into `state.data`; manually reading the request stream will hang
* ''Tags are arrays'': TW stores tags as arrays internally, not strings ŌĆö use `Array.isArray()` check when reading from `tiddler.fields.tags`
* ''Syncer timing'': after `addTiddler()`, the file appears on disk after the next syncer tick (typically a few seconds)
* ''Template field values are filters'': if you want a literal string as output, wrap it in double brackets: `[[my literal value]]`
* ''Action widgets need `$tw.fakeDocument`'': server-side action execution requires a real `Widget` instance (not the duck-typed fake used for filter evaluation)
* ''CLI wrapper write target'': `$tw.boot.wikiTiddlersPath` points to `mywiki-cli/tiddlers/` when using the wrapper ŌĆö the deserializer resolves the first `includeWikis` entry to write to `mywiki/tiddlers/` instead
* ''`$:/StoryList` in wrapper'': the syncer writes `$:/StoryList` to `mywiki-cli/tiddlers/` during CLI runs ŌĆö this is harmless junk, can be gitignored

