<!-- ===== COMMAND REPLY ===== -->

<$reveal stateTitle="$:/state/rimir/ext-connect/examples-tab" type="match" text="command-reply" default="command-reply">

!! Answering a command (full round-trip)

An external tool processes a command tiddler from `ext-outbox/` and sends the result back. The inbound pipeline links the answer to the original command.

!!! Setup

The command tiddler (created via `@Dodo` field or inline `@Dodo` text) sits in `ext-outbox/` with these fields:

|!Field |!Value |!Source |
|`target` |`Dodo` |Set by text-command extraction |
|`command-text` |`process` |Value of the `@Dodo` field |
|`source` |`MyNote` |Original tiddler title |
|`status` |`pending` |Auto-set |
|`stream-type` |`default` |Set by user before saving |

The rule `stream-reply-default` matches when `context.0.fields.stream-type` equals `default`.

!!! Inbound JSON

The external tool sends back the processed result with the command tiddler as context:

```json
{
  "text": "Here is the processed result",
  "context": ["MyNote/@Dodo/20260309130505927"]
}
```

```
TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1 npx tiddlywiki dev-wiki --import input.json application/x-rimir-ext-connect
```

!!! What happens

# ''Default profile'' ŌåÆ title becomes `Inbox/<timestamp>`, tagged `Inbox`
# ''Rule matches'' ŌåÆ `stream-reply-default` fires because the context tiddler has `stream-type: default`
# ''Template applied'' ŌåÆ `parent` field set to the command tiddler's title
# ''Post-creation action'' ŌåÆ the command tiddler's `stream-list` field gets the new tiddler's title appended

!!! Result

The new tiddler at `Inbox/<timestamp>`:

|!Field |!Value |
|`text` |`Here is the processed result` |
|`tags` |`Inbox` |
|`parent` |`MyNote/@Dodo/20260309130505927` |

The command tiddler now has:

|!Field |!Value |
|`stream-list` |`Inbox/20260309140000000` |

!!! Overrides

The external tool can override any field:

```json
{
  "text": "Here is the processed result",
  "title": "Dodo/Response/2026-03-09",
  "context": ["MyNote/@Dodo/20260309130505927"],
  "fields": {"status": "complete", "confidence": "high"}
}
```

`body.title` wins over the template-generated title. `body.fields` merge on top of everything.

</$reveal>

<!-- ===== BASIC PUSH ===== -->

<$reveal stateTitle="$:/state/rimir/ext-connect/examples-tab" type="match" text="basic">

!! Basic tiddler push

Minimal input ŌĆö creates a tiddler using the `default` profile template:

```json
{"text": "Hello from external tool"}
```

```
TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1 npx tiddlywiki dev-wiki --import input.json application/x-rimir-ext-connect
```

''Result'': tiddler created at `Inbox/<timestamp>` with the `Inbox` tag (from the default profile template).

</$reveal>

<!-- ===== TITLE & FIELDS ===== -->

<$reveal stateTitle="$:/state/rimir/ext-connect/examples-tab" type="match" text="fields">

!! Explicit title and fields

Override the generated title and add custom fields:

```json
{
  "text": "Meeting with the team about Q2 roadmap",
  "title": "Meetings/2026-03-05 Q2 Roadmap",
  "fields": {
    "tags": "Meeting Q2",
    "attendees": "Alice Bob Carol"
  }
}
```

''Result'': tiddler at `Meetings/2026-03-05 Q2 Roadmap` with explicit tags and custom `attendees` field. Explicit `fields` override template-generated values.

</$reveal>

<!-- ===== CONTEXT ===== -->

<$reveal stateTitle="$:/state/rimir/ext-connect/examples-tab" type="match" text="context">

!! Context resolution

Pass context tiddlers so templates and rules can reference their fields:

```json
{
  "text": "This is a reply to the stream",
  "context": ["MyProject/Stream"]
}
```

The `context` array names existing wiki tiddlers. Their fields become available as variables in template filter expressions:

|!Variable |!Value |
|`context-titles` |Space-separated list of context titles |
|`context.0.title` |Title of the first context tiddler |
|`context.0.fields.tags` |Tags field of the first context tiddler |
|`context.0.fields.<any-field>` |Any field from the first context tiddler |

A rule might match on context: `[enlist<context-titles>has[streams-default]limit[1]]` ŌĆö if any context tiddler has a `streams-default` field, the rule fires and selects a stream-reply template.

</$reveal>

<!-- ===== ACTIONS ===== -->

<$reveal stateTitle="$:/state/rimir/ext-connect/examples-tab" type="match" text="actions">

!! Post-creation actions

Template tiddlers can have action widgets in their `text` field that execute after the tiddler is created. Example template:

```
title: $:/config/rimir/ext-connect/tpl/stream-reply
out.title: [<context.0.title>addsuffix[/]addsuffix<timestamp>]
out.tags: [[StreamReply]]
parent: [<context.0.title>]

<$action-listops $tiddler=<<context.0.title>> $field="list" $subfilter="[<new-title>]"/>
```

When a tiddler is created with this template:

# `out.title` ŌåÆ generates title from context + timestamp
# `out.tags` ŌåÆ adds `StreamReply` tag
# `parent` ŌåÆ set to the context tiddler's title
# `text` (actions) ŌåÆ appends the new tiddler's title to the parent's `list` field

The `new-title` variable is only available in the action phase (after the tiddler is saved).

</$reveal>

<!-- ===== RULES ===== -->

<$reveal stateTitle="$:/state/rimir/ext-connect/examples-tab" type="match" text="rules">

!! Rule-based matching

Rules are evaluated in order ŌĆö first match wins. Each rule has a TW `filter` and one or more `templates`:

```json
[
  {
    "name": "stream-reply-default",
    "filter": "[<context.0.fields.stream-type>match[default]]",
    "templates": ["$:/config/rimir/ext-connect/tpl/stream-reply-default"]
  },
  {
    "name": "discussion-reply",
    "filter": "[enlist<context-titles>tag[Discussion]limit[1]]",
    "templates": ["$:/config/rimir/ext-connect/tpl/discussion-reply"]
  }
]
```

With `"context": ["SomeTiddler"]`:

* If `SomeTiddler` has `stream-type: default` ŌåÆ `stream-reply-default` matches ŌåÆ sets `parent`, appends to `stream-list`
* If `SomeTiddler` is tagged `Discussion` ŌåÆ `discussion-reply` matches ŌåÆ uses `tpl/discussion-reply`
* If neither matches ŌåÆ no rule-derived fields (profile + explicit fields still apply)

</$reveal>

</$fill>
