<$fill $name="body">

!! Protocol field spec

ext-connect uses a fixed set of field names shared across the wiki-side JS modules, the Python connector, and the resolution pipeline. These field names are ''not configurable'' ŌĆö they form a tightly coupled contract between all components.

!!! Inbound JSON payload (POST body / CLI `--import`)

|!Field |!Required |!Type |!Description |
|`text` |Yes |string |Tiddler content body |
|`title` |No |string |Explicit title (overrides template-generated title) |
|`profile` |No |string |Profile name from `$:/config/rimir/ext-connect/profiles` |
|`context` |No |string[] |Tiddler titles loaded from wiki store for rule matching and variable building |
|`fields` |No |object |Explicit field overrides, merged after template/rule evaluation |

!!! Text-command tiddler fields (ext-outbox)

Created by `text-command.js` when extracting `@Target` commands from tiddler text. These `.tid` files land in `ext-outbox/` for external tools to pick up.

|!Field |!Value |!Notes |
|`title` |`<OriginalTitle>/@<Target>/<timestamp>` |Auto-generated composite title |
|`tags` |Outbox tag (default: `ext-outbox`) |Configurable via `$:/config/rimir/text-command/outbox-tag` |
|`text` |Extracted command text |Same content as `command-text` |
|`source` |Title of originating tiddler |Links reply back to origin |
|`target` |Target name (e.g. `LLM`) |Case-sensitive, must be in registered targets list |
|`command-text` |Extracted command text |Duplicate of `text` for explicit field access |
|`status` |`pending` |Updated by external tools: `pending` ŌåÆ `processing` ŌåÆ `done` / `error` |
|`type` |`text/vnd.tiddlywiki` | |
|`created` |TW timestamp | |
|`modified` |TW timestamp | |

!!! Status lifecycle

```
pending ŌåÆ processing ŌåÆ done
                     ŌåÆ error
```

Set by external tools (e.g. Python connector). The wiki-side view template reflects status changes live.

!!! Template output fields (`out.` prefix)

|!Field pattern |!Behavior |
|`out.<fieldname>` |Strip `out.` prefix; value evaluated as TW filter ŌåÆ output field |
|Non-reserved field |Output field directly; value evaluated as TW filter |
|Reserved field |Skipped as output (template metadata only) |
|`text` (body) |Collected as action widget markup, executed after tiddler creation |

Reserved fields (never output): `title`, `text`, `type`, `tags`, `created`, `modified`, `creator`, `modifier`, `bag`, `revision`

!!! Variables (available in template filters and actions)

|!Variable |!Scope |!Description |
|`timestamp` |filters + actions |UTC `YYYYMMDDHHMMSSMMM` |
|`profile` |filters + actions |Profile name from request (empty string if absent) |
|`context-titles` |filters + actions |Space-separated list of context tiddler titles |
|`context.<N>.title` |filters + actions |Title of Nth context tiddler (0-indexed) |
|`context.<N>.fields.<X>` |filters + actions |Field X of Nth context tiddler |
|`new-title` |actions only |Title of the just-created tiddler |

!!! Auto-generated output fields

|!Field |!Value |!Condition |
|`title` |`Inbox/<timestamp>` |Only if not set by template, rule, or explicit override |
|`type` |`text/vnd.tiddlywiki` |Only if not already set |
|`created` |Current TW timestamp |Only if not already set |
|`modified` |Current TW timestamp |Always set/overwritten |

!!! Config tiddlers

|!Tiddler |!Type |!Purpose |
|`$:/config/rimir/ext-connect/profiles` |`application/json` |Profile name ŌåÆ template tiddler title mapping |
|`$:/config/rimir/ext-connect/rules` |`application/json` |Ordered rules: filter + template tiddler titles |
|`$:/config/rimir/text-command/targets` |`application/json` |Registered target names for `@Target` extraction |
|`$:/config/rimir/text-command/outbox-tag` |text |Tag for command tiddlers (default: `ext-outbox`) |
|`$:/config/rimir/text-command/scan-filter` |text |Filter determining which tiddlers are scanned for commands |
|`$:/config/rimir/text-command/view-template` |text |Template rendered inline where commands were extracted |
|`$:/config/rimir/text-command/delegate` |wikitext |Cascade dispatcher for context rendering |

!!! Python connector field mapping

The Python `tw_connector` library maps `.tid` fields to dataclass attributes:

|!.tid field |!Python `Command` attr |!Type |
|`title` |`title` |`str` |
|`target` |`target` |`str` |
|`command-text` |`command_text` |`str` |
|`source` |`source` |`str` |
|`status` |`status` |`CommandStatus` enum |
|`text` |`text` |`str` |
|`created` |`created` |`str` |
|`modified` |`modified` |`str` |
|(file path) |`file_path` |`Path` |
|(all fields) |`fields` |`dict[str, str]` |
|(rendered) |`context` |`str | None` |

The `Reply` dataclass maps back to the inbound JSON payload: `text`, `title`, `profile`, `context` (list[str]), `fields` (dict).

---

!! CLI import (`--import`) ŌĆö primary inbound path

Import tiddlers via the CLI using the same JSON format and resolution pipeline:

```
TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1 npx tiddlywiki mywiki --import input.json application/x-rimir-ext-connect
```

Set `TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1` so the filesystem-watcher skips startup and the process exits cleanly. Tiddler files are written directly to `mywiki/tiddlers/` (respecting `$:/config/FileSystemPaths`).

|!Argument |!Value |
|`wiki-folder` |`mywiki` |
|`filepath` |Path to a JSON file with the request payload |
|`deserializer` |`application/x-rimir-ext-connect` (custom MIME type) |

Input JSON format (identical to POST body):

|!Field |!Required |!Type |!Description |
|`text` |Yes |string |Tiddler content |
|`title` |No |string |Explicit title (overrides generated title) |
|`profile` |No |string |Named profile from profiles config |
|`context` |No |string[] |Tiddler titles for rule matching (read from wiki store at import time) |
|`fields` |No |object |Explicit field overrides (merged after rules) |

Console output on success:

```
ext-connect: created "Inbox/20260304120000000" ŌåÆ /path/to/file.tid
```

Notes:

* No running server required ŌĆö `--import` boots TW from disk, runs deserializer, exits
* `TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1` prevents filesystem-watcher from keeping the process alive
* `.tid` file written directly to `mywiki/tiddlers/` (respects `$:/config/FileSystemPaths`)
* If a server is running, filesystem-watcher detects the new file and syncs to browser
* Post-creation actions execute identically to the POST path
* Returns 0 tiddlers to `--import` (self-save pattern) ŌĆö see architecture docs

---

!! POST /api/ext-connect/put-tiddler (fallback ŌĆö may be deprecated)

Request body (JSON):

|!Field |!Required |!Type |!Description |
|`text` |Yes |string |Tiddler content |
|`title` |No |string |Explicit title (overrides generated title) |
|`profile` |No |string |Named profile from profiles config |
|`context` |No |string[] |Tiddler titles for rule matching |
|`fields` |No |object |Explicit field overrides (merged after rules) |

Required headers:

|!Header |!Value |
|`Content-Type` |`application/json` |
|`X-Requested-With` |`TiddlyWiki` |

Success response (200):

```json
{
    "status": "ok",
    "title": "Inbox/20260304120000000"
}
```

Error responses:

|!HTTP |!Condition |
|400 |Invalid JSON body |
|400 |Missing required `text` field |
|403 |Missing `X-Requested-With` header |
|500 |Internal processing error |

!! Profiles config

Tiddler: `$:/config/rimir/ext-connect/profiles` (type: `application/json`)

Maps profile names to template tiddler titles:

```json
{
    "default": "$:/config/rimir/ext-connect/tpl/default",
    "meeting-note": "$:/config/rimir/ext-connect/tpl/meeting-note"
}
```

The `default` profile is used when no profile is specified in the request.

!! Rules config

Tiddler: `$:/config/rimir/ext-connect/rules` (type: `application/json`)

```json
[
    {
        "name": "rule-name",
        "filter": "[enlist<context-titles>has[some-field]limit[1]]",
        "templates": ["$:/config/rimir/ext-connect/tpl/some-template"]
    }
]
```

Rules are evaluated in array order. First matching rule wins.

|!Field |!Description |
|`name` |Human-readable rule name |
|`filter` |TW filter expression ŌĆö non-empty result means match |
|`templates` |Array of template tiddler titles, evaluated in order (later overrides earlier for fields; actions concatenated) |

!! Template tiddler reference

Template tiddlers define output fields via TW filter expressions.

!!! Field naming

|!Field pattern |!Behavior |
|`out.fieldname` |Strip `out.` prefix ŌåÆ output field name; value evaluated as TW filter |
|non-reserved field |Output field directly; value evaluated as TW filter |
|reserved field |Skipped as output (template metadata) |

Reserved fields (skipped): `title`, `text`, `type`, `tags`, `created`, `modified`, `creator`, `modifier`, `bag`, `revision`

!!! Field evaluation

* ''`tags` output'' (after prefix stripping): all filter results joined via `$tw.utils.stringifyList()`
* ''All other fields'': first filter result used as value
* ''Conflict resolution'': if both `out.parent` and `parent` exist, the `out.` version wins

!!! Example template tiddler

```
title: $:/config/rimir/ext-connect/tpl/stream-reply
out.title: [<context.0.title>addsuffix[/]addsuffix<timestamp>]
out.tags: [[StreamReply]]
parent: [<context.0.title>]

<$action-listops $tiddler=<<context.0.title>> $field="list" $subfilter="[<new-title>]"/>
```

* `title` ŌåÆ skipped (reserved ŌĆö template's own identity)
* `text` ŌåÆ skipped as output, executed as post-creation actions
* `out.title` ŌåÆ strip prefix ŌåÆ output `title` = filter result
* `out.tags` ŌåÆ strip prefix ŌåÆ output `tags` = all filter results as TW string list
* `parent` ŌåÆ not reserved ŌåÆ output `parent` = first filter result

!! Post-creation actions

The `text` field of template tiddlers contains action widget markup executed server-side after the new tiddler is saved.

All variables available during filter evaluation are available, plus:

|!Variable |!Value |
|`new-title` |Title of the just-created tiddler |

Supported action widgets include `<$action-setfield>`, `<$action-listops>`, `<$action-deletefield>`, and any other widget that operates via `$tw.wiki` methods.

!! Variables available in filters and actions

|!Variable |!Available in |!Value |
|`context-titles` |filters + actions |Space-separated list of context tiddler titles (via `$tw.utils.stringifyList`) |
|`context.0.title` |filters + actions |Title of first context tiddler |
|`context.N.fields.X` |filters + actions |Field X of Nth context tiddler |
|`timestamp` |filters + actions |UTC `YYYYMMDDHHMMSSMMM` |
|`profile` |filters + actions |Profile name from request |
|`new-title` |actions only |Title of the just-created tiddler |

!! Resolution pipeline

Shared by both POST and CLI `--import` paths:

# Build variables map from context tiddlers + request
# Profile template: evaluate fields ŌåÆ base output
# Rule evaluation: first-match filter ŌåÆ evaluate template fields ŌåÆ merge into output; collect action text
# `body.fields` from request ŌåÆ explicit overrides
# `body.title` / `body.text` from request ŌåÆ always win
# Fallback title: `Inbox/<timestamp>` if still missing
# Default `type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki` if missing
# Save tiddler to wiki store
# ''POST path'': syncer mismatch triggers file write on next tick
# ''CLI path'': `saveTiddlerToFileSync` writes `.tid` directly to `mywiki/tiddlers/`
# Execute collected action text with `new-title` variable added
# Persist any tiddlers modified by actions (syncer mismatch or direct disk write)

---

!! Text-command syntax (outbound)

!!! Single-line command

```
@Target command text here
```

`@Target` followed by a space and non-whitespace characters on the same line. The entire line after `@Target ` is the command text.

!!! Multi-line command

```
@Target
Multi-line command text.
Can span multiple lines.
Target@
```

`@Target` on its own line (optionally followed by whitespace), content until a closing `Target@` line.

!!! Registered targets

Tiddler: `$:/config/rimir/text-command/targets` (type: `application/json`)

```json
["LLM", "Dodo"]
```

Only these strings are recognized as targets. Unregistered `@strings` are left as-is.

!!! Scan filter

Tiddler: `$:/config/rimir/text-command/scan-filter`

```
[tag[process]]
```

Only tiddlers matching this filter are scanned for `@Target` commands on save.

!!! Outbox tag

Tiddler: `$:/config/rimir/text-command/outbox-tag`

Default: `ext-outbox`. Must match the `$:/config/FileSystemPaths` routing rule.

!!! Command tiddler fields

|!Field |!Value |
|`title` |`<OriginalTitle>/@<Target>/<timestamp>` |
|`tags` |Outbox tag |
|`text` |Extracted command text |
|`source` |Title of originating tiddler |
|`target` |Target name (e.g. `LLM`) |
|`command-text` |Extracted command text |
|`status` |`pending` ŌĆö external tools update this |

!!! View template

Tiddler: `$:/config/rimir/text-command/view-template`

Rendered inline where the command was extracted. The `currentTiddler` is the command tiddler (set by the `<$tiddler>` wrapper). Fields like `status` update live when modified by external tools.

---

!! Context rendering (`--render`)

External tools render context for command tiddlers using TW's `--render` command with the delegate template:

```
npx tiddlywiki mywiki --render "[[CmdTitle]]" "[[output.txt]]" "text/plain" "$:/config/rimir/text-command/delegate"
```

|!Argument |!Value |
|`title` |Command tiddler title (wiki-syntax `[[...]]`) |
|`output` |Output filename (written to `mywiki/output/`) |
|`type` |`text/plain` ŌĆö raw text, no HTML wrapping |
|`template` |`$:/config/rimir/text-command/delegate` ŌĆö cascade dispatcher (plain tiddler title, not filter syntax) |

!! Delegate template

Tiddler: `$:/config/rimir/text-command/delegate`

Uses `:cascade` to select a context render template based on the command tiddler's fields. The `currentTiddler` is the command tiddler title (set by `--render`).

!! Cascade selectors

Tagged `$:/tags/rimir/text-command/context-template`, sorted by `order` field (ascending). Each tiddler's `text` is a filter expression:

* Receives the command tiddler as input
* Returns the title of a context render template if it matches
* First non-empty result wins

|!Selector |!Order |!Filter |
|`llm` |100 |`[all[current]get[target]match[LLM]then[$:/config/rimir/text-command/ctx/llm]]` |
|`dodo` |200 |`[all[current]get[target]match[Dodo]then[$:/config/rimir/text-command/ctx/dodo]]` |
|`default` |9999 |`[all[current]then[$:/config/rimir/text-command/ctx/default]]` |

!! Context render templates

Wikitext tiddlers that produce plain-text output. `currentTiddler` is the command tiddler. Available fields via transclusion:

|!Field |!Description |
|`target` |Target name (e.g. `LLM`) |
|`command-text` |The extracted command text |
|`source` |Title of the originating tiddler |
|`text` |Command text (same as `command-text`) |
|`status` |Command status (e.g. `pending`) |

Templates can transclude the source tiddler's content with `<$transclude tiddler={{!!source}} field="text"/>`.

!! Adding a new target context

# Create a cascade selector tiddler:
#* Tag: `$:/tags/rimir/text-command/context-template`
#* `order` field: number (lower = higher priority, before 9999 default)
#* `text`: filter expression returning a context template title
# Create a context render template tiddler:
#* Wikitext producing the desired plain-text output
#* `currentTiddler` is the command tiddler

No JS changes or server restart needed.

</$fill>
</$transclude>
