<$fill $name="body">

!! tiddlerdeserializer module type

`deserializer.js` registers the custom MIME type `application/x-rimir-ext-connect`. TiddlyWiki's `--import` command looks up deserializers by MIME type and calls them with the raw file content. The deserializer parses JSON and runs the resolution pipeline.

!! $tw.utils.saveTiddlerToFileSync

Used by the CLI path to write `.tid` files directly to disk. Combines `generateTiddlerFileInfo()` (which respects `$:/config/FileSystemPaths` routing rules) with synchronous file writing. The server's syncer is not involved.

!! $tw.syncer.tiddlerInfo / changeCount

The POST path uses a syncer mismatch pattern: after `addTiddler()`, it sets `tiddlerInfo[title].changeCount` to `wiki.getChangeCount() - 1`. The syncer detects the mismatch on its next tick and writes the file to disk. This is the inverse of filesystem-watcher's pattern (which matches counts to prevent writes).

!! invokeActionString

Server-side action execution uses `$tw.rootWidget.invokeActionString()` with a real `Widget` instance and `$tw.fakeDocument` (TW's server-side fake DOM). This enables action widgets like `<$action-listops>` and `<$action-setfield>` to execute without a browser environment.

!! th-saving-tiddler hook

The `text-command.js` module hooks `th-saving-tiddler` to intercept tiddler saves in the browser. When a saved tiddler matches the scan filter, it extracts `@Target` commands, creates command tiddlers, and replaces the command text with transclusion markup ŌĆö all before the save completes.

!! $:/config/FileSystemPaths

A system tiddler containing filter expressions that route tiddlers to subdirectories on disk. The `filesystem-paths-setup.js` startup module prepends a rule for outbox-tagged tiddlers so command tiddlers land in `tiddlers/ext-outbox/`.

!! includeWikis

The CLI wrapper (`mywiki-cli/tiddlywiki.info`) uses `includeWikis` to reference the main wiki read-only. TiddlyWiki merges the included wiki's tiddler store, plugins, and config into the wrapper. The deserializer resolves the first `includeWikis` entry to determine the correct write target for `.tid` files.

</$fill>
</$transclude>
