<!-- ===== CLI TAB ===== -->

<$reveal stateTitle="$:/state/rimir/ext-connect/settings-tab" type="match" text="cli" default="cli">

!! CLI import (`--import`) ŌĆö primary inbound path

Import tiddlers via CLI ŌĆö no running server needed. This is the recommended way to push tiddlers from external tools.

```
TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1 npx tiddlywiki mywiki --import input.json application/x-rimir-ext-connect
```

Set `TIDDLYWIKI_CLI_MODE=1` so the filesystem-watcher skips startup and the process exits cleanly.

!!! JSON format

|!Field |!Required |!Type |!Description |
|`text` |Yes |string |Tiddler content |
|`title` |No |string |Explicit title (overrides generated title) |
|`profile` |No |string |Named profile from profiles config |
|`context` |No |string[] |Tiddler titles for rule matching |
|`fields` |No |object |Explicit field overrides (merged after rules) |

!!! Notes

* `.tid` files are written directly to `mywiki/tiddlers/` (respects `$:/config/FileSystemPaths`)
* If a server is running, filesystem-watcher detects the new file and syncs to browser
* Post-creation actions execute identically to the POST path

</$reveal>

<!-- ===== REFERENCE TAB ===== -->

<$reveal stateTitle="$:/state/rimir/ext-connect/settings-tab" type="match" text="reference">

!! Variables available in filters and actions

|!Variable |!Available in |!Value |
|`context-titles` |filters + actions |Space-separated list of context tiddler titles |
|`context.0.title` |filters + actions |Title of first context tiddler |
|`context.N.fields.X` |filters + actions |Field X of Nth context tiddler |
|`timestamp` |filters + actions |UTC `YYYYMMDDHHMMSSMMM` |
|`profile` |filters + actions |Profile name from request |
|`new-title` |actions only |Title of the just-created tiddler |

---

!! Template field convention

|!Field pattern |!Behavior |
|`out.fieldname` |Strip `out.` prefix ŌåÆ output field; value evaluated as TW filter. Use for reserved names (`title`, `tags`, `type`, etc.) |
|non-reserved field |Output field directly; value evaluated as TW filter |
|reserved field (`title`, `text`, `type`, `tags`, `created`, `modified`, ...) |Skipped as output (belongs to the template itself) |
|`text` (template body) |Executed as action widgets after tiddler creation |

For `tags` output: all filter results joined as TW string list. For all other fields: first filter result used.

---

!! Resolution pipeline (merge order)

# Profile template fields ŌåÆ base output
# Rule templates (first-match) ŌåÆ merge into output; collect action text
# `body.fields` from request ŌåÆ explicit overrides
# `body.title` / `body.text` from request ŌåÆ always win
# Fallback title: `Inbox/<timestamp>` if still missing
# Default `type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki` if missing
# Save tiddler ŌåÆ execute collected actions

</$reveal>
